        i? Primary vs secondary storage -- what are they?
            To persist data for a long time, including across phone restarts and relaunches of application or programs
        ii? Advantages and disadvantages of storage types
            Solid State Drive
            Because it is fast and responsive, and can store more data in less space (is compact), which is suitable for a smartphone as it requires compactness; and because it has no moving parts, so is less likely to break, which is also desirable as it is harder to repair a smartphone.
