4.
    a?
        There is a header including the destination IP address and packet number. This is used to route the packet (send the packet to the correct destination) as well as to resassemble the initial data after the packet is received.
        There is a body containing the data for the packet. This is a section of the email-data.
        There is a footer containing the source IP address.
    b.
        i.
            Full duplex because employees may need to send each other emails at once. Full duplex allows for simultaneous transmission in both directions. Parallel allows for faster speed of transmission of data, as many bits of data are sent at the same time. This is useful as the time employees will have to spend waiting for an email to be sent/waiting to receive an email will result in lost productivity so should be minimized.
        ii? advantages and disadvantages of all forms of data transmission
            1. Parallel data transmission may be hard to implement and to synchronize; and may go out of sync.
            2. Full duplex data transmission is often more expensive than half-duplex.
        iii.
            Parallel half duplex data transmission
